im to three National Championships, 25 conference championships, two conference division championships, 11 Division I-A bowl berths, and four undefeated, untied seasons. Following the [[2018 Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football team|2018 regular season]], the Louisiana Tech football program has posted 620 all-time wins and an all-time winning percentage of .570. Currently, the Bulldogs are coached by [[Skip Holtz]].\n\n==Seasons==\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"22%\"\n! colspan=2|Legend\n|-\n|\n{{Color box|#CCFFFF|border=darkgray}} <sup>\u2020</sup> National Champions<br>\n{{Color box|#FFCCCC|border=darkgray}} <sup>\u2021</sup> Conference Champions<br>\n{{Color box|#D8BFD8|border=darkgray}} <sup>#</sup> Division Champions<br>\n{{Color box|#ffe6bd|border=darkgray}} ^ Division I-A bowl game berth<br>\n{{Color box|#ddffdd|border=darkgray}} * Non-Division I-A postseason berth<br>\n|}</center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; width:98%;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:5%;\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12%;\"|Coach\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:13%;\"|Conference\n!colspan=\"4\"|Season results\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:37%;\"|Bowl/Playoff result\n!colspan=\"1\" style=\"width:8%;\"|Final ranking\n|-\n!Conference finish\n!Wins\n!Losses\n!Ties\n!NCAA Poll\n|-\n|align=\"center\" Colspan=\"11\" style=\"background: #002F8B;\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Louisiana Tech Bulldogs'''</span>\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[1901 Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football team|1901]]\n|align=\"center\"|[[Edwin Barber]]\n|align=\"center\"|Independent\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|align=\"center\"|0\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[1902 Louisiana Tech Bulldogs football team|1902]]\n|align=\"center\"|[[Frank Singleton (coach)|Frank Singleton]]<br>[[Howard F. Crandell]]\n|align=\"center\"|Independent\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|align=\"cent