eral Party of Canada|Liberal Party]] and [[Progressive Party of Canada|Progressive Party]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3% (1926)\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Liberal|row}}\n|[[Liberal Protectionist]]\n|1925||{{dts|1930}}\n|Anti-[[free trade]], [[protectionism]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Independent|row}}\n|[[McCarthyite candidates 1896|McCarthyite]]\n|1896||{{dts|1898}}\n|Anti-Catholic, anti-French, British imperialism\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| {{sort|0.5|<1% (1896)}}\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|National|row}}\n| [[National Party of Canada]] (II)\n|1991||{{dts|1994}}\n| [[Canadian nationalism]], [[protectionism]], [[progressivism]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Independent|row}}\n|Nationalist\n|1873||{{dts|1910}}\n| socialist, nationalization of industries\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1% (1887)\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Conservative (historical)|row}}\n|Nationalist\n|1903||{{dts|1963}}\n|Various parties and candidates\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| \n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1% (1887)\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Conservative (historical)|row}}\n|[[Nationalist Conservative]]\n|1878||{{dts|1911}}\n|\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| {{sort|0.5|<1% (1891)}}\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|Natural Law|row}}\n| [[Natural Law Party of Canada]]<br /><small>{{lang|fr|Parti de la loi naturelle du Canada}}</small>\n| 1992||{{dts|23 January 2004}}<ref>http://www.elections.ca/content.aspx?section=pol&dir=par&document=index&lang=e#Natural</ref>\n| [[New age]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0\n{{Canadian party colour|CA|NLFirst|row}}\n| [[Newfoundland and Labrador First Party]]\n| 2007||{{dts|31 January 2011}}<ref>http://www.elections.ca/content.aspx?section=pol&dir